  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Beautician",
  "description": "<p>We are seeking a versatile and passionate <strong>Beautician</strong> to join our team. As an \"All-Rounder,\" you will play a key role in providing a diverse range of personal care treatments, from rejuvenating facial therapies to professional nail services. Our focus is on delivering high-quality, personalized experiences that leave our clients feeling confident and refreshed.</p><h3><strong>Job Description</strong></h3><p>In this role, you will be the face of our service excellence. Your day-to-day responsibilities will include:</p><ul><li><p><strong>Skincare & Body Treatments:</strong> Perform professional facials, skin analysis, and body treatments tailored to client needs (anti-aging, hydration, deep cleansing, etc.).</p></li><li><p><strong>Nail Artistry:</strong> Provide full-service manicures and pedicures, including gel application, acrylics, nail shaping, and creative nail art.</p></li><li><p><strong>Consultation & Sales:</strong> Conduct thorough consultations to understand client goals and recommend appropriate treatments and home-care products.</p></li><li><p><strong>Sanitation & Safety:</strong> Maintain a pristine workstation by sterilizing tools and following strict hygiene protocols in line with industry standards.</p></li><li><p><strong>Client Management:</strong> Build and maintain strong relationships with regular clients, ensuring a high level of customer retention and satisfaction.</p></li><li><p><strong>Operational Support:</strong> Assist with inventory management, salon tidiness, and occasional appointment scheduling.</p></li></ul><h3><strong>Job Requirements</strong></h3><p>To be successful in this role, you should possess a blend of technical skill and interpersonal charm:</p><ul><li><p><strong>Experience:</strong> Minimum of 1–2 years of experience in a salon or spa environment.</p></li><li><p><strong>Technical Proficiency:</strong></p><ul><li><p>Proven expertise in <strong>Manicure/Pedicure</strong> services.</p></li><li><p>Solid understanding of <strong>Skin Physiology</strong> and various facial techniques.</p></li></ul></li></ul><ul><li><p><strong>Certification:</strong> Relevant beauty certification (e.g., CIDESCO, ITEC, CIBTAC, or local equivalent vocational training).</p></li><li><p><strong>Soft Skills:</strong></p><ul><li><p>Excellent communication and active listening skills.</p></li><li><p>A calm, professional demeanor with a focus on hospitality.</p></li><li><p>Punctuality and a strong sense of responsibility.</p></li></ul></li><li><p><strong>Flexibility:</strong> Ability to work on weekends and public holidays (peak periods for beauty services).</p></li></ul>",
